ou need to discover the exact article title for an entity you have not yet identified.  \n   - Use **`lookup_wikipedia`** when you already know the exact title and need the article text (or a specific fact) from it.  \n   - Use **`finish`** *only* when you have retrieved the full text of all three required Wikipedia pages (or you are certain no more relevant pages exist).  \n5. **Provide `next_tool_args`** as a **single‑line JSON object** matching the tool’s schema, e.g. `{"query": "…"} ` or `{"title": "…"} `. Do not include any extra whitespace or comments.  \n6. **Avoid unnecessary calls:** once a title is known and its page has been looked up, do not search for it again. Do not retrieve pages that are not directly needed to confirm the three entities.  \n7. **When calling `finish`**, leave `next_tool_args` empty (`{}`); the subsequent extraction module will read the trajectory and output the final list of titles.\n[3] **Output format (exactly as shown, one field per line):**\n[4] ```\n\nOutput (JSON only):'}], 'image_urls': []}, response={'token_ids': [4913, 291, 1199, 66582, 453, 3252, 8156, 16221, 2198, 1252, 788, 16, 1335, 1318, 3252, 334, 55291, 369, 279, 32710, 4688, 28654, 7859, 11, 34682, 1464, 1790, 5854, 2450, 11, 1790, 22785, 1269, 11, 1790, 22785, 8384, 63, 1648, 334, 220, 16, 13, 4457, 279, 3717, 15516, 13, 64547, 279, 2326, 14744, 429, 525, 20975, 9733, 476, 51773, 2567, 311, 15442, 279, 3717, 13, 220, 17, 13, 1374, 19991, 279, 34682, 311, 8253, 892, 14744, 614, 1012, 30403, 323, 1128, 374, 2058, 7402, 13, 220, 18, 13, 3377, 6334, 1565, 3600, 5854, 2450, 63, 438, 264, 2805, 11, 14175, 11652, 27798, 5098, 11, 34948, 279, 9664, 5387, 11, 323, 25021, 279, 1790, 5392, 13, 220, 19, 13, 8427, 1565, 3600, 22785, 1269, 63, 504, 1565, 1836, 1670, 14939, 7808, 1565, 21020, 1670, 14939, 7808, 476, 1565, 30150, 28587, 220, 20, 13, 39565, 1565, 3600, 22785, 8384, 63, 438, 264, 3175, 8447, 4718, 13, 220, 21, 13, 34006, 47732, 6738, 13, 220, 22, 13, 5443, 1565, 301